The problem is that using the OEM's app and servers is mandatory.<br>
All 'smart'/IoT devices should, by law, have a simple way of configuring the server adress it talks to via an open protocol like MQTT.<br>
This way, you could easily block it at your firewall if you'd wanted to, and let it talk to some local smart home controller.</div>
